args: You want to embark on a mission\nbeyond the Halidom?
That's right. Princess Zethia told us of a\nfacility built to study other worlds.
She said they were researching how to\nclose the rifts between worlds.
Yes, until the facility fell under attack.\nMost everything inside it was destroyed.
The chances of finding anything useful\nare sadly quite slim.
They could be as slim as string, but that\ndoesn't change anything! A chance is\na chance!
Captain, you told us we needed to band\ntogether to forge a brighter future.
Well, we put our heads together,\nand we decided that right now\nthis is our best shot!
Hmm... You're right that we need to\nconsider our next move.
Closing the rifts between worlds would\nbe a sizable boon...
Very well. We shall strike out for that\nfacility—on the condition that each of\nyou returns alive. Understood?
This place has certainly seen better days.\nYou're sure this is the facility?
Yes. If memory serves, there should be a\nsecret vault deep inside.
We may well be walking into untold\ndanger. Please, be careful.
It's a modified fiend! I didn't think they'd\nstill be here... We need to get out of here!
What?! We can't just run out empty-handed\nnow!
Leave the fiend to us. You focus on finding\nthe info we came for!
Nothing you say will sway them now.\nDon't worry, they'll have my support—\nnow go!

(There's as good a chance as not that we
find the information we're looking for, but
after seeing their determination I must
leave no stone unturned!)
Rrgh! Come on! We just have to hold out\na bit longer!
I'm fine. Leave the rest to me!
Yes! We did it! Is everyone okay?
We've two with broken ribs, and a few\nothers with scrapes and sprains.
Forgive me. As leader, I take full\nresponsibility for all injuries.
Come on, Captain, don't be daft! We were\nthe ones who begged to come here. I just\nhope it wasn't all for nothing.
*pant* These are documents on the\nUncanny Gate!
You mean the gate that connects Askr with\nother worlds?!

Most likely. 300 years ago, the Dyrenell
Empire is said to have built a replica of
that gate and conversed with royalty from
another world.

This is a record of the research they
conducted to do so. If we use this to
create a gate of our own, we could
change the tide of our fate completely.

The tears between worlds have
destabilized this land greatly;
with a gate we could get things
back under control.
We could save our world from ruin.
We fought hard and took our fair share\nof knocks... But it was all worth it.
Yes. Together, we WILL realize the future\nof hope!

Once we've seen to our wounded, we
should make haste back to the Halidom.
I think everyone there could stand to
hear some good news.
Did you hear? Princess Zethia and the\nShepherds found a way to save the world!
Yeah! If it works, we won't have to worry\nabout fiends anymore! We can play\nwherever we want!
I wanna see what it's like outside\nthe Halidom!
I know, dear. And that means we need to\nsupport Princess Zethia's research. What\ndo you say we go pick some fruit for her?
Man, the hope around here is tangible!\nWe can't let anyone wipe those smiles\naway ever again.
We will defeat any foe who would interrupt\nyour research, Princess. Of that you have\nmy word.
Thank you, Chrom. The answers we seek\nare close, I can feel—
Sounds like we have company. I'll head\nfor the castle gate—to arms, Shepherds!
Stay here, Princess! You're our last hope,\nand we won't let any harm come to you!
Heh, of course! We have to see this future\nwe're fighting for, after all!
It seems Thórr will stop at nothing to deny\nthis world a bright future.
But I won't give up. As empress, I stole\ncountless lives—but now, everyone here\nhas entrusted me with theirs.
So let's keep going, Zethia. Let's keep\nfighting for the future you deserve.
You have brought us together, and so\nlong as we have those bonds, I shall\nnot give up!
